# AI Development Instructions

## CRITICAL: Minimal Architecture Protection

‚ö†Ô∏è **MANDATORY PRESERVATION RULES** ‚ö†Ô∏è

This project maintains a **MINIMAL ESSENTIAL ARCHITECTURE** that must be preserved at all costs.

### NEVER DELETE OR REMOVE:
- Any existing files in the project structure
- Any existing dependencies in package.json
- Any existing scripts in package.json
- Any configuration files (rollup.config.js, tauri.conf.json, etc.)
- Any existing directories or their contents

### ALLOWED MODIFICATIONS:
- ‚úÖ Add new files
- ‚úÖ Add new dependencies
- ‚úÖ Add new scripts
- ‚úÖ Modify existing file content (but never delete files)
- ‚úÖ Extend existing configurations
- ‚úÖ Create new directories
- ‚úÖ use only the current running server on port 3000

### FORBIDDEN ACTIONS:
- ‚ùå Delete any existing files
- ‚ùå Remove any existing dependencies
- ‚ùå Remove any existing npm scripts
- ‚ùå Restructure the core architecture
- ‚ùå Replace existing build system components
- ‚ùå do not add any concole.log
- ‚ùå do not start any new server

### Core Architecture Components:
- **Svelte Frontend**: Rollup-based build system with custom configuration
- **Fastify Backend**: Node.js server with CORS support
- **Tauri Desktop**: Cross-platform desktop application wrapper
- **Development Toolchain**: Custom shell scripts (dev.sh, run_*.sh)
- **Asset Management**: Organized media files (audio, images, videos, fonts)
- **Hybrid Structure**: Seamless integration between web and native components

### Current Essential Dependencies:
```json
{
  "svelte": "^5.33.14",
  "rollup": "^4.42.0", 
  "rollup-plugin-svelte": "^7.2.2",
  "fastify": "^5.3.3",
  "@fastify/cors": "^11.0.1",
  "@tauri-apps/cli": "^2.4.0"
}
```

### Essential Scripts:
- `dev`: Launch development environment
- `build:svelte`: Build Svelte components
- `watch:svelte`: Watch mode for Svelte
- `start:server`: Start Fastify server
- `tauri:dev`: Tauri development mode

**When suggesting changes, always ADD to the existing structure, never REPLACE or REMOVE.**

### Framework Philosophy:
This is the **Squirrel Framework** üêøÔ∏è - a hybrid modern framework combining:
- Modern Svelte 5 frontend
- High-performance Fastify backend
- Cross-platform Tauri desktop capabilities
- Minimal yet complete development stack

Every component has been carefully selected and integrated. The current structure represents the absolute minimum viable architecture for this hybrid framework to function properly.
